http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/Forgery-case-against-14/article14011727.ece

GVMC has lodged a complaint with the Madhurawada police against 14 persons for submitting forged documents to get houses under JNNURM.The houses have been allotted to those who lost houses in the expansion of road from the highway to YSR Nagar.It was proved that the beneficiaries submitted forged documents and got the houses allotted following which criminal case was filed, Urban Community Development Project Director D. Srinivasan said.In a separate instance, a cheating case was filed with the Pendurti police against a person for collecting Rs. 1.45 lakh from five persons promising them houses under JNNURM.